  • Field Details

    • MB

      public static final int MB
      Message Begin. The MB flag is a 1-bit field that when set indicates the start of an NDEF message.
      See Also:
      Constant Field Values

    • ME

      public static final int ME
      Message End. The ME flag is a 1-bit field that when set indicates the end of an NDEF message. Note, that in case of a chunked payload, the ME flag is set only in the terminating record chunk of that chunked payload.
      See Also:
      Constant Field Values

    • CF

      public static final int CF
      Chunk Flag. The CF flag is a 1-bit field indicating that this is either the first record chunk or a middle record chunk of a chunked payload.
      See Also:
      Constant Field Values

    • SR

      public static final int SR
      Short Record. The SR flag is a 1-bit field indicating, if set, that the PAYLOAD_LENGTH field is a single octet. This short record layout is intended for compact encapsulation of small payloads which will fit within PAYLOAD fields of size ranging between 0 to 255 octets.
      See Also:
      Constant Field Values

    • IL

      public static final int IL
      ID_LENGTH field is present. The IL flag is a 1-bit field indicating, if set, that the ID_LENGTH field is present in the header as a single octet. If the IL flag is zero, the ID_LENGTH field is omitted from the record header and the ID field is also omitted from the record.
      See Also:
      Constant Field Values

    • TNF_MASK

      public static final int TNF_MASK
      Type Name Format Mask. The TNF field value indicates the structure of the value of the TYPE field.
      See Also:
      Constant Field Values
